                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">soulrot</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;08/01/2003&nbsp;: 12:55:17 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> "My tip to you is to go to echo caverns and melee the needlites using your damage shield until you ding 29 and then give fearkiting another go."<br /><br />Couldn't agree more, nice loot, nice exp, easy kills with the Damage Shield.<br /><br />And yes, fear kiting is all but inefficient (IMO) till lvl 34 with Invoke Fear (42 seconds).  And Venom of the Snake is just vicious at that lvl.  I didn't fear kite till lvl 34.  Pre-lvl 29 I usually would pull with Heat Blood, sent pet, then cast the lvl 12 Lifetap DoT (Leach), then get in there and melee the mob, with a weapon in primary.  My defense skills were capped for my lvl back then so I had ok AC and was able to do this without too much trouble.  When I was taking too much damage, I'd back up off of mob (with pet taunt ON) and lifetap and then get back into the mix.<br /><br />At lvl 34 you can do the Rangers at the Druid Rings in WC most likely, or perhpas the guards at the tollbooth too for some good practice fear kiting.<br /><br />Study your spells, use a calculator if you have to to figure out which one is more efficient, and check out lucy.fnord.net to learn about resist adjusts and such.  Heart Flutter the lvl 16 DoT for example, is a good bit less efficient than the lvl 12 Heat Blood DoT, and does less dmg too for example.<br /><br />Good Luck =)</span></font></td>
